</div>
</div>
</section>
<!-- End Services Section -->
<!-- ======= Projects Section ======= -->
<section class="projects" id="projects">
<div class="container" data-aos="fade-up">
<div class="section-header">
<h2>Our Projects</h2>
</div>
<div class="portfolio-isotope" data-portfolio-filter="*" data-portfolio-layout="masonry" data-portfolio-sort="original-order">
<ul class="portfolio-flters" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100">
<li class="filter-active" data-filter="*">All</li>
<li data-filter=".filter-rubber-lining">
                Rubber Lining &amp; Corrosion Protection
              </li>
<li data-filter=".filter-civil-works">
               Civil Works (Design, Build &amp; Maintain) 
              </li>
<li data-filter=".filter-structural-steel-fabrication-welding">
                Structural Steel Fabrication &amp; Welding</li>
</ul>
<div class="row gy-4 portfolio-container" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="200">
<div class="col-lg-4 col-md-6 portfolio-item filter-rubber-lining filter-structural-steel-fabrication-welding">
<div class="card portfolio-content h-100">
<img alt="Evander Gold Mine Lowered CIL Tank Structure" class="card-img-top" src="assets/img/projects/Evander Gold Mine Lowered CIL Tank Structure.png"/>
<div class="card-body">
<h5 class="card-title">
                      Evander Gold Mine Lowered CIL Tank Structure
                    </h5>
<p class="card-text">
<span style="font-weight: bold">scope:</span> We performed a structural and corrosion‑protection upgrade to a lowered
carbon‑in‑leach tank. Tasks included structural assessment, surface preparation and coating
application. The team evaluated the integrity of the tank shell and support beams, removed
degraded coatings, repaired corrosion damage and applied a high‑build epoxy system. This
upgrade increased the tank’s service life and ensured compliance with plant safety standards.
                    </p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<!--  Start of projects item 2 -->
<div class="col-lg-4 col-md-6 portfolio-item filter-rubber-lining filter-structural-steel-fabrication-welding">
<div class="card portfolio-content h-100">
<img alt="Air Liquide Antennastructural Frame Design" class="card-img-top" src="assets/img/projects/Air Liquide Antennastructural Frame Design.png"/>
<div class="card-body">
<h5 class="card-title">
                      GOVAN MBEKI MUNICIPALITY – WATER
INFRASTRUCTURE REHABILITATION
                    </h5>
<p class="card-text">
<span style="font-weight: bold">scope:</span>Rehabilitated aging water reservoirs and
pipeline infrastructure to support local service delivery. The scope included structural
inspections, concrete repairs, replacement of corroded reinforcing steel and installation of new
liners. In parallel, pipelines were upgraded with corrosion-resistant coatings and leak detection
systems. These upgrades align with South Africa’s push for public‑private partnerships and
infrastructure development, ensuring reliable water supply for the municipality.
                    </p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<!--  End of projects item 2 -->
<div class="col-lg-4 col-md-6 portfolio-item filter-rubber-lining">
<div class="card portfolio-content h-100">
<img alt="Air Liquide Antennastructural Frame Design" class="card-img-top" src="assets/img/projects/Air Liquide Antennastructural Frame Design.png"/>
<div class="card-body">
<h5 class="card-title">
                     ELIKHULU CIL TANK RUBBER LINING
                    </h5>
<p class="card-text">
<span style="font-weight: bold">scope:</span>Performed a complete refurbishment of a carbon-in-leach (CIL) tank at Elikhulu. The
scope included abrasive blasting to SA 2.5 to remove old coatings, soluble-salt testing, and
profile checks. After surface preparation, we applied a multi-layer natural rubber lining
designed to withstand cyanide-rich slurry, using specialised adhesives and vulcanisation. Final
quality assurance involved spark testing, adhesion pull-off tests and thickness mapping to verify
integrity and longevity.
                    </p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="col-lg-4 col-md-6 portfolio-item filter-structural-inspection">
<div class="card portfolio-content h-100">
<img alt="Air Liquide Antennastructural Frame Design" class="card-img-top" src="assets/img/projects/Air Liquide Antennastructural Frame Design.png"/>
<div class="card-body">
<h5 class="card-title">
                     ELIKHULU SLURRY PIPELINES &amp; LAUNDERS
                    </h5>
<p class="card-text">
<span style="font-weight: bold">scope:</span>Protected Elikhulu’s slurry transport system. We dismantled existing
pipelines and launders, prepared the internal surfaces with grit blasting and solvent cleaning
and installed abrasion-resistant rubber linings with dovetail joints at flange areas to prevent
delamination. The work covered over 1 km of pipework and multiple launders feeding to
thickeners. Holiday testing and hydrostatic pressure tests ensured there were no defects or leaks
before recommissioning.
                    </p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="col-lg-4 col-md-6 portfolio-item filter-rubber-lining">
<div class="card portfolio-content h-100">
<img alt="Evander Gold Mine Workshop Building Structural Inspection" class="card-img-top" src="assets/img/projects/Evander Gold Mine Workshop Building Structural Inspection.png"/>
<div class="card-body">
<h5 class="card-title">
                      ELIKHULU THICKENER UNDERFLOW SUMPS &amp; PUMP HOUSINGS
                    </h5>
<p class="card-text">
<span style="font-weight: bold">scope:</span> Applied hard-rubber linings to the underflow sumps, feed wells and pump
casings associated with Elikhulu’s thickeners. We performed high-pressure water jetting to
remove scale and corrosion, followed by grit blasting and priming. Linings were custom‑fitted to
complex geometries and cured on site using temperature-controlled methods. The use of
elastomeric linings has significantly increased equipment life in high-abrasion zones and
reduced maintenance downtime.
                    </p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="col-lg-4 col-md-6 portfolio-item filter-structural-steel-fabrication-welding">
<div class="card portfolio-content h-100">
<img alt="Elikhulu Tank Steel Platform" class="card-img-top" src="assets/img/projects/Elikhulu Tank Steel Platform.png"/>
<div class="card-body">
<h5 class="card-title">ELIKHULU PREGNANT SOLUTION AND OVERFLOW TANKS</h5>
<p class="card-text">
<span style="font-weight: bold">scope:</span> Refurbished and lined the pregnant-solution tanks and overflow piping at Elikhulu. The
project involved internal scaffolding, blasting to achieve a near‑white metal finish and
installation of bromobutyl rubber linings resistant to cyanide-rich solutions. Welds and seams
were carefully sealed, and spark testing ensured a continuous lining. External surfaces received
a three‑coat epoxy system to comply with corrosivity category C5 coatings.
                    </p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="col-lg-4 col-md-6 portfolio-item filter-civil-works">
<div class="card portfolio-content h-100">
<img alt="Sasol New Pipeline Unit Rubber Lining" class="card-img-top" src="assets/img/projects/Sasol New Pipeline Unit Rubber Lining.png"/>
<div class="card-body">
<h5 class="card-title">
                      Sasol New Pipeline Unit Rubber Lining
                    </h5>
<p class="card-text">
<span style="font-weight: bold">scope:</span> protected a new pipeline unit carrying aggressive chemicals. Our team
performed surface preparation, selected appropriate lining materials and installed
chemical‑resistant rubber linings inside pipelines, elbows and fittings. Adhesion promoters and
tie‑coats were applied to ensure a robust bond, and spark testing was conducted to detect
pinholes. The project extended the life of the pipeline system and reduced the risk of leaks and
contamination.
                    </p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="col-lg-4 col-md-6 portfolio-item filter-civil-works">
<div class="card portfolio-content h-100">
<img alt="Eskom Cooling Towers Planned Maintenance" class="card-img-top" src="assets/img/projects/Eskom Cooling Towers Planned Maintenance.png"/>
<div class="card-body">
<h5 class="card-title">
                      Eskom Cooling Towers Planned Maintenance
                    </h5>
<p class="card-text">
<span style="font-weight: bold">scope:</span> provided safe access and maintenance for cooling towers at a power
station. We designed and erected modular scaffolding systems compliant with SANS 10085‑1,
enabling inspection of tower internals and drift eliminators. The scope included dismantling and
reinstallation of fill pack components, concrete repairs to tower shells and application of
protective coatings. All work was scheduled during a short outage to minimise impact on power
generation.
                    </p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="col-lg-4 col-md-6 portfolio-item filter-civil-works">
<div class="card portfolio-content h-100">
<img alt="Air Liquide Antennastructural Frame Design" class="card-img-top" src="assets/img/projects/Air Liquide Antennastructural Frame Design.png"/>
<div class="card-body">
<h5 class="card-title">
                      Air Liquide Antenna Structural Frame Design
                    </h5>
<p class="card-text">
<span style="font-weight: bold">scope:</span> designed and fabricated a new steel frame to support antennas at an Air Liquide
facility. The scope involved structural analysis, detailed design in accordance with SANS 10162‑1,
fabrication of steel sections and on‑site installation. Galvanising (SANS 121) and a three‑coat
paint system were applied for corrosion protection. The project delivered a stable and
long‑lasting structure for critical communication equipment.
                    </p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
